			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2021</a> paper:</span><br><i>Automating the synthesis of recommender systems for modelling languages</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/LissetteAlmonte.html">Lissette Almonte</a>, <a href="../profile/SaraPérezSoler.html">Sara Pérez-Soler</a>, <a href="../profile/EstherGuerra.html">Esther Guerra</a>, <a href="../profile/IvánCantador.html">Iván Cantador</a>, <a href="../profile/JuandeLara.html">Juan de Lara</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3486608.3486905">10.1145/3486608.3486905</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagM">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> The paper mainly targets domain-specific languages or modeling languages, including their design or use.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It includes substantial tool support or infrastructure relevant for engineering/using languages.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagL">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> It relies on formal methods (definitions/proofs/semantic properties) beyond informal description.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5e.html"><span class="tagL">T5E: Empirical Evaluation</span></a><ul><li> It reports an empirical evaluation (experiments, study, benchmarks, or measurements).
</li></ul></li></ul>
